<div id="review_4283156010" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4283156010" />
    <a title="Justin Matthews" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/92187764-justin-matthews"><img alt="Justin Matthews" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611367830p2/92187764.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4283156010?book_show_action=true">Oct 12, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Justin Matthews" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Justin Matthews" href="/user/show/92187764-justin-matthews">Justin Matthews</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4283156010" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1986591135086819220">While modern historians might have more resources at their disposal (though, not *living* resources), not enough can be said for earlier writers like Tuchman, Manchester, and, of course, Cornelius Ryan, who can just flat-out write. Easily the best book on D-Day I&apos;ve read to date.</span>
  <span id="freeText1986591135086819220" style="display:none">While modern historians might have more resources at their disposal (though, not *living* resources), not enough can be said for earlier writers like Tuchman, Manchester, and, of course, Cornelius Ryan, who can just flat-out write. Easily the best book on D-Day I've read to date.</span>
